cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.NE 

This paper discusses reinforcement learning algorithms and their theoretical properties, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), systems and control (cs.SY), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper specifically focuses on potential-based shaping, which is a technique used in reinforcement learning, further supporting the likelihood of these sub-categories.
